---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import LinkedInIcon from "../components/icons/LinkedInIcon.astro";
import { CURRENT_YEAR, LINKEDIN_URL } from "../utils/constants";
import { getUrl } from "../utils/url";
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Coen Claassen · About"
  description="Background and approach of Coen Claassen focused on zero to one product work fast learning and building under uncertainty."
>
  <Header />

  <main>
    <h5 class="bold spacer-8">Hey, I'm Coen. <span class="thin">I turn early, risky ideas into real, manufacturable products.</span></h5>
    
    <p class="post-h3 thin spacer-4">Much of my work happens before there's certainty.<br class="desktop-only"> I navigate hard trade-offs early when decisions quietly lock in years of consequence.</p>

    <section class="spacer-6 two-column">
      <div class="column-left">
        <h1 class="post-h4 bold">I get things that matter from vision to reality.</h1>
        <p class="p-grid thin spacer-3">I've taken products from first sketch to certified, production-ready systems by making the work visible long before it was comfortable.</p>
        <p class="p-grid thin spacer-2">Prototypes are central to how I work. They turn opinions into discussions, and discussions into decisions.</p>
        <p class="p-grid thin spacer-2">Depending on the situation, I act as a sparring partner, a hands-on builder, or an embedded product lead.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="column-right">
        <h1 class="post-h4 bold">Where others hesitate,<br class="desktop-only"> I lean in.</h1>
        <p class="p-grid thin spacer-3">Breakthrough ideas are born fragile.<br class="desktop-only"> They are too early, too risky, and hard to defend.</p>
        <p class="p-grid thin spacer-2">Most don't fail in the market.<br class="desktop-only"> They fail earlier – in the fog of doubt, risk, and resistance.</p>
        <p class="p-grid thin spacer-3">This is where I lean in:</p>
        <ul class="p-grid thin spacer-2">
          <li>When teams stall and you need clarity and momentum.</li>
          <li>When technical, design, and business needs to come together.</li>
          <li>When you need startup speed and a path to yes.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="spacer-6">
      <h1 class="cta bold">I find a path to yes<br class="desktop-only"> and build what proves it.</h1>
      <div class="buttons-stacked spacer-4">
        <a href={getUrl("")} class="btn-grey thin">See my work</a>
        <a href={getUrl("work")} class="btn-grey thin">How I work</a>
        <a href={LINKEDIN_URL} class="btn-black thin" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          <LinkedInIcon />
          Connect
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer year={CURRENT_YEAR} class="spacer-7" />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .two-column {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--spacer-5);
  }

  .column-left,
  .column-right {
    width: 100%;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .two-column {
      flex-direction: row;
      gap: 0;
    }

    .column-left {
      width: 37.5%;
      padding-right: 2rem;
    }

    .column-right {
      width: 62.5%;
    }
  }

  /* Buttons side by side */
  .buttons-stacked {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: row;
    gap: var(--spacer-2);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .buttons-stacked button {
    width: 100%;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .buttons-stacked {
      align-items: flex-start;
    }

    .buttons-stacked button {
      width: auto;
    }
  }

  /* Add vertical spacing between top and hamburger menu on mobile */
  @media (max-width: 767px) {
    :global(header) {
      padding-top: var(--spacer-2);
    }
  }

</style>

